				<p>Do you have these circumstances pulled up in your mind? Great! You’re in the right headspace for what’s coming next.</p><h2>1. Lead by Serving</h2><p>This first video is a television commercial for a bank in Thailand — and it was certainly created with the intent to pull at one’s heart strings. However, it is also certainly moving and worth the time to remind restaurant executives ascribed to servient leadership that the road is often long and thankless for all committed to contributing in a meaningful way. It’s not about small and short-term payoffs. It’s about setting an example that eventually wins not only hearts and minds but also makes a difference that lasts in a company or community and ripples out far wider than may be imagined when putting in the hard work day to day.</p>					</div>
